<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="493" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Head and thorax pale ochraceous, forewings creamy white. Crown and facial sutures darker, one spot on either side of median line on posterior margin of crown, dark brown. Median area on anterior half of pronotum infuscated.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Crown without median carina, keel on frontoclypeus prominent and projecting slightly more on ventral region. Pronotum with median carina on anterior half, sublateral carinae absent, surface coarsely pitted.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis box="[199,366,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer dorsal margin convex and declivous posteriorly, ventral margin concave in middle, anterior margin with well-developed tergal apodemes; ventral process arising at midventral region, with large base, tapering to pointed apex, exceeding dorsal margin of pygofer, its surface with a few microsetae. Valve anterior margin triangularly produced. Subgenital plate triangular, with a few microsetae, three times as long as wide at base. Style with apophysis curved laterally, apex pointed, ventral margin with series of rugae. Connective Y-shaped with stem longer than arms. Aedeagus with ventral process articulated with connective, in lateral view posterior 0.33 curved dorsally and narrowed to pointed apex, in dorsal view stem shorter than arms; shaft with sclerotized pigmented ventral region, rest membranous and unpigmented, dorsal apodeme well developed and bifid, gonopore apical. Segment X large, membranous, sternite posteriorly produced and bilobed, with anterior and posterior process (
<figureCitation box="[250,348,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 140 – 150" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1839,1862]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,206,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1435,193,1819]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 140 – 150. Signoretia quoinensis sp. nov. 140. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 141. Pygofer ventral process, lateral view; 142. Valve and subgential plate, ventral view; 143. Connective, dorsal view; 144. Sternite and processes of segment X, ventral view; 145. Aedeagus, anterodorsal view; 146 – 147. Style, lateral and dorsal view; 148. Aedeagus and ventral process, lateral view; 149. Ventral process of aedeagus, ventral view; 150. Female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167204/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Fig. 144</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis box="[199,393,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite wider than long, abruptly narrowed in posterior 0.25, posterior margin shallowly concave with rounded lateral margins. First and second pair of valvulae as in 
<figureCitation box="[1134,1263,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 91 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,211,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[164,1408,193,1875]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 91 – 97. Female ovipositor and male genitalia of species of Signoretia. 91 – 93. S. quoinensis sp. nov. 91. Ovipositor, lateral view; 92. Apex of first pair of valvula; 93. Apex of second pair of valvula. 94 – 96. S. sinuata sp. nov. 94. Ovipositor, lateral view; 95. Apex of first pair of valvula; 96. Apex of second pair of valvula. 97. Male genital capsule of S. maculata Baker, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167198/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Figs 91–93</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
