<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="493" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Remarks</emphasis>
. The female specimen is only tentatively associated with the male. 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1278,1051,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quoinensis">
<emphasis box="[1124,1138,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1158,1278,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">quoinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">S. delicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having the pygofer ventral process uniformly and gradually tapering and the sternum of segment X specialised (
<figureCitation box="[416,515,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 140 – 150" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1839,1862]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,206,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1435,193,1819]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 140 – 150. Signoretia quoinensis sp. nov. 140. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 141. Pygofer ventral process, lateral view; 142. Valve and subgential plate, ventral view; 143. Connective, dorsal view; 144. Sternite and processes of segment X, ventral view; 145. Aedeagus, anterodorsal view; 146 – 147. Style, lateral and dorsal view; 148. Aedeagus and ventral process, lateral view; 149. Ventral process of aedeagus, ventral view; 150. Female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167204/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Fig. 144</figureCitation>
